 \lim_{x\to\infty} \frac{\Gamma(x+1,x(1+\epsilon))}{x\Gamma(x)}=0 
\Gamma(x,a) = \int_a^\infty t^{x-1}e^{-t} \mathrm{d}t
\Gamma(x) = \Gamma(x,0)
 \lim_{x\to\infty} \frac{\int_{x(1+\epsilon)}^\infty t^{x-1}\log(1+t)e^{-t} \mathrm{d}t}{x\Gamma(x)}=0 
